Shim: cutlass.utils.ampere_helpers for cutlass-dsl >= 4.4.2

cutlass-dsl 4.4.2 removed cutlass.utils.ampere_helpers, but flash-attn-4
(FA4 beta7) still imports it for SMEM_CAPACITY["sm80"]. This shim provides
the missing constant so FA4 can import cleanly.

Apply:
  cp ampere_helpers.py "$(python3 -c "import cutlass.utils; print(cutlass.utils.__path__[0])")/ampere_helpers.py"

--- /dev/null
+++ b/nvidia_cutlass_dsl/python_packages/cutlass/utils/ampere_helpers.py
@@ -0,0 +1,7 @@
+# Shim for flash_attn.cute compatibility with cutlass-dsl >= 4.4.2
+# which removed this module. Only SMEM_CAPACITY is referenced.
+SMEM_CAPACITY = {
+    "sm80": (164 - 1) * 1024,
+    "sm86": (100 - 1) * 1024,
+    "sm89": (100 - 1) * 1024,
+}
